-- Abbott's Coalition Overtakes Government in Poll for First Time Since Vote
-- B y   N i c h o l a   S a m i n a t h e r
-- 2010-10-25T19:56:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-25/abbott-s-coalition-overtakes-government-in-poll-for-first-time-since-vote.html
Australia’s opposition Coalition has
overtaken the Labor government in popularity for the first time
since the Aug. 21 election, a Newspoll opinion survey showed. On
a two-party preferred basis, Labor had 48 percent voter support,
compared with 52 percent for the Liberal-National coalition,
according to a telephone survey of 1,141 voters from Oct. 22 to
24 published in the Australian newspaper. Satisfaction with
Prime Minister  Julia Gillard’s performance dropped 4 percentage
points to 44 since the last poll between Oct. 8 and 10, while
opposition lead er Tony Abbott’s rose 2 points to 41 percent.
The poll had a margin of error of 3 percentage points.  To contact the reporter on this story:
